Mauritius’s Gamma Rises Most in 19 Months on Special Dividend

-- B y   K a m l e s h   B h u c k o r y
-- 
2011-07-19T07:19:09Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-19/mauritius-s-gamma-rises-most-in-19-months-on-special-dividend.html
Gamma Civic Ltd. (GML) , Mauritius’s
largest construction company by market value, jumped the most in
19 months after saying it will pay a special dividend.  The stock advanced as much as 13 percent, the biggest jump
since December 2009, and traded up 6.9 percent to 481 rupees at
11:06 a.m in Port Louis the capital. A close at that level would
be the highest since July 1995.  Gamma will pay a special dividend of 40 rupees per share on
or about Aug. 30, the company said in a statement on the Stock
Exchange of Mauritius website published after the close of
trading yesterday.  To contact the reporter on this story:
